      "content": "Those sound like classic rendering artifacts rather than signs of mental illness, as skybox glitches often occur due to weathering bugs, texture looping issues, or GPU driver conflicts. They are quite common in older games or those running on overclocked hardware, especially when light-shading calculations get messed up. It might be worth trying a clean install of the game or updating your graphics drivers to fix the problem. If the glitches persist after these steps, it could indicate more serious system instability, but it's rarely something psychological.",
